NSAIDs you may be familiar with are <a href="https://www.relievet.com/blogs/tips/aspirin-for-dogs-alternatives-and-side-effects" target="_self" rel="nofollow" style="text-decoration-line: underline;">Aspirin</a>, Ibuprofen, and <a href="/blogs/tips/side-effects-of-naproxen-for-dogs-alternatives" target="_self" rel="nofollow" style="text-decoration-line: underline;">Naproxen</a>; they are generally considered pain relievers.
<br><br>Galliprant can be used alone post-surgery for pain relief, while Gabapentin needs to be used with other pain medications like NSAIDs and opioids to relieve pain.
<br><br>Gabapentin is a prescription medication referred to as a gamma-aminobutyric acid (GABA) analog. GABA reduces the volatility of nerve cells (neurons) in the brain, which plays a role in seizures and the transmission of pain signals. Familiar GABAs include Lyrica, Neurontin, Horizant, and Gralise.
<br><br>Gabapentin is also known as an anticonvulsant drug, also referred to as an anti-elliptic drug. In some cases, Gabapentin is used to manage acute postoperative pain and sedation for dogs post-surgery.</span></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-9441" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-bSqaIl hxsZTX pf-46_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-hkgtus clVJp"><div class="sc-bBHHxi gGMCwe pf-47_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-JkixQ lbFEmW pf-48_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-avest eSTvWa pf-49_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hGnimi cpnKBf pf-51_">H2: Which is better at treating arthritis pain for dogs?</span></h2><p class="sc-hYQoXb koTnzq pf-52_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hGnimi cpnKBf pf-54_">Galliprant targets the pain receptors associated with arthritis, while Gabapentin is used for neuropathic pain that does not respond to nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drugs (NSAIDs) or opiates.
<br><br>Galliprant does not inhibit homeostatic functions and allows for cell growth and the body's healing processes. The Department of Biomedical and Biotechnological Sciences, School of Medicine, University of Catania, wrote Gabapentin might be beneficial within the treatment of inflammatory situations associated with ocular pain, including uveitis.
<br><br>Further studies need to be done on Gabapentin's effects on arthritis pain and homeostatic functions of the healing process.</span></p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-1160" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-bSqaIl hxsZTX pf-55_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-hkgtus clVJp"><div class="sc-bBHHxi gGMCwe pf-56_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-JkixQ lbFEmW pf-57_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-avest eSTvWa pf-58_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hGnimi cpnKBf pf-60_">Gabapentin and Galliprant together for dogs</span></h2><p class="sc-hYQoXb koTnzq pf-61_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hGnimi cpnKBf pf-63_">It is safe to give both medications at once. Galliprant is an anti-inflammatory medication for arthritis in dogs, safe and well-received.
<br><br>Gabapentin is an anti-seizure medication, but when used in low doses, it helps relieve pain.
<br><br>Veterinarians often use Gabapentin combined with Galliprant to provide even better pain control from arthritis.
<br><br>This union of medications is called Multimodal pain relief and is a common practice in veterinary medicine.</span></p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-1435" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-bSqaIl hxsZTX pf-64_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-hkgtus clVJp"><div class="sc-bBHHxi gGMCwe pf-65_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-JkixQ lbFEmW pf-66_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-avest eSTvWa pf-67_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hGnimi cpnKBf pf-69_">Gabapentin vs. Galliprant Usage Chart</span></h2><div class="sc-igXgud kxFdJE pf-70_ pf-table-default" data-pf-type="Table"><table><tbody><tr><th class="A1"><span>Medical Usage</span></th><th class="B1"><span>Anxiety</span></th><th class="C1"><span>Controls Symptoms of Osteoarthritis</span></th><th class="D1"><span>Fever</span></th><th class="E1"><span>Inflammation</span></th><th class="F1"><span>Pain</span></th><th class="G1"><span>Post-Surgery</span></th><th class="H1"><span>Seizures</span></th><th class="I1"><span>Long-Term Use</span></th></tr><tr><td class="A2"><span>Gabapentin</span></td><td class="B2"><span>X</span></td><td class="C2"><span>X</span></td><td class="D2"><span>X</span></td><td class="E2"><span>X</span></td><td class="F2"><span>X</span></td><td class="G2"><span></span></td><td class="H2"><span>X</span></td><td class="I2"><span></span></td></tr><tr><td class="A3"><span>Galliprant</span></td><td class="B3"><span></span></td><td class="C3"><span>X</span></td><td class="D3"><span>X</span></td><td class="E3"><span>X</span></td><td class="F3"><span>X</span></td><td class="G3"><span>X</span></td><td class="H3"><span></span></td><td class="I3"><span>X</span></td></tr></tbody></table></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-f073" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-bSqaIl hxsZTX pf-71_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-hkgtus clVJp"><div c